$ PowerShell: the preference variable $progressPreference
@ $progressPreference

The value of the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference `$progressPreference` controls the behavior of the `→ Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/progress/write`.
-
The possible values that the variable can be set to some of the `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/ActionPreference` enumeration.

sa:
  Setting the value of `$progressPreference` to `silentlyContinue` when using `→ Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/webRequest/invoke` to download (large) files makes it
  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/webRequest/invoke#invoke-webRequest-slow[significantly faster].
